(A U B) x C = (A x C) U (B x C) = {(1, a), (1, b), (1, c), (2, a), (2, b), (2, c), (3, a), (3, b), (3, c), (x, a), (x, b), (x, c), (y, a), (y, b), (y, c)}

Thus, we have proven that the Cartesian product of (A U B) x C is equal to the Cartesian product of (A x C) U (B x C).
